President Barack Obama has proclaimed November 2015 as Military Family Month in the United States. In his proclamation, he acknowledges the sacrifices made by military families and expresses gratitude for their service. He emphasizes that the United States is stronger and safer because of the millions of military family members who selflessly give up time with their loved ones. The President also highlights the efforts of his administration to support military families through initiatives such as Joining Forces, which connects military spouses with employment opportunities. He calls on all Americans to honor military families through private actions and public service. The proclamation serves as a recognition of the contributions and sacrifices made by military families in defense of the nation.